        body: 'When December arrives and you\'re setting next year\'s target, you now have data to make it realistic rather than aspirational. Your month-by-month revenue shows your seasonal pattern. Your job volume trend shows your demand growth rate. Your ATV trend shows whether you\'re moving up or down the value spectrum. A realistic target is your current run rate, adjusted for: planned improvements (better marketing, new services, corporate accounts), seasonal factors, and competitive changes in your market. A stretch target is 10-15% above your realistic target — the number you\'ll hit if everything goes well. Know the difference and plan accordingly.',
